    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 2000 4000 and 8000 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        SPEEDOMETER/TACHOMETER, GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 9800 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - GAUGE CLUSTERS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>GAUGE CLUSTERS</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove Gauge Clusters</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Always disconnect the battery negative cable before servicing the various clusters and their
                        components.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Batteries expel explosive gases. Keep sparks, flames, burning cigarettes, or other ignition
                        sources away at all times. Always wear safety glasses and a face shield when working near
                        batteries to prevent personal injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Remove air from the vehicle primary and secondary systems when removing clusters with air
                        gauges.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0824505">Figure 5</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0824506">Figure 6</hotlnk>
                for the following:
            </para>
            <figure id="f0824505" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/g0824505.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Cluster Bezel Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. ATTACHING SCREWS (4 PLACES)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. GAUGE CLUSTER BEZEL PLATE (LEFT)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0824506" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/g0824506.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Cluster Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. GAUGE CLUSTER (RIGHT)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. RETAINING TAB (BOTH SIDES)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0824507" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/g0824507.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Gauge Electrical Connector</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. GAUGE CLUSTER (RIGHT)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. ELECTRICAL CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. LIGHT SOCKETS (11 PLACES)</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. MECHANICAL GAUGE FITTING (2 PLACES)</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. CLUSTER RETAINING TABS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0824508" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/g0824508.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Gauge Mechanical Connector</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. GAUGE LINE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SWIVEL FITTING</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. GAUGE CLUSTER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0824509" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/g0824509.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Gauge Fitting Lock Plate</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. GAUGE CLUSTER (RIGHT)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FITTING LOCK PLATE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0824510" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/g0824510.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Line Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. GAUGE LINE FITTING FLATS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. GAUGE LINE FITTING OPENING</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove screw in the cluster corners and remove the cluster bezel plate (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0824505">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pry retaining tabs to remove cluster from instrument panel. Use care not to break tabs (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0824506">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect electrical connector (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0824507">Figure 7</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If cluster is equipped with mechanical gauges, loosen gauge lock nut (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0824508">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate gauge line lock plate (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0824509">Figure 9</hotlnk>), and twist gauge line fitting so flats on fitting will
                    align with opening on cluster, and remove line (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0824510">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cluster from vehicle.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install Gauge Clusters</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position cluster near opening in instrument panel. Twist gauge line fitting until flats
                    on fitting align with opening in cluster and install fitting.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position gauge line lock plate and tighten locknut.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect electrical connector and install cluster in instrument panel making sure locking
                    tabs are fully engaged.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position cluster bezel plate and tighten screws.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
